    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p> <p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong>\u00a0over a medium-high heat</p> <p>Once hot, add the <strong>chicken breast<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> and cook for 3 min on each side or until golden</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-chicken-orzo-and-spring-greens-broth/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve the <strong>chicken stock cube<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in 900ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[1.8L]</span><strong> boiled water\u00a0</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-chicken-orzo-and-spring-greens-broth/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>orzo pasta</strong> and <strong>chicken stock</strong> to the pan and cook for 8 min\u00a0</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-chicken-orzo-and-spring-greens-broth/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, rip the leaves off the<strong> spring greens</strong>, discard the tough stalks, then layer the leaves over each other, roll them up and slice into very thin strips</p> <p>Slice the thin strips in half lengthways</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-chicken-orzo-and-spring-greens-broth/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the <strong>orzo</strong> has been cooking for 8 min, add the <strong>sliced spring greens</strong> to the pan and cook for 4-5 min further</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-chicken-orzo-and-spring-greens-broth/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop the <strong>lemon<span style=\"color:#e86754;\">\u00a0</span></strong>in half</p> <p>Shave half of the\u00a0<strong>Italian hard cheese</strong>\u00a0with a peeler, until you end up with a pile of\u00a0cheese shavings\u00a0</p> <p>Grate the <span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>remaining</strong></span><strong>\u00a0cheese</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-chicken-orzo-and-spring-greens-broth/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the <strong>chicken</strong> is cooked (no pink meat!), remove it\u00a0from the pan and transfer it to a board, then shred it apart, using two forks \u2013 this technique is known as 'pulling'</p> <p>Return the <strong>shredded chicken</strong> to the pan with the <strong>classic basil nut\u00a0</strong><strong>pesto</strong>, <strong>grated cheese</strong>\u00a0(reserve the shavings!) and the <span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>juice</strong></span> of 1/2\u00a0<span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span> <strong>lemon</strong></p> <p>Season with <strong>salt</strong>\u00a0and\u00a0<strong>pepper </strong>\u2013<strong>\u00a0</strong>this is your <strong>chicken &amp; orzo broth\u00a0</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-chicken-orzo-and-spring-greens-broth/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> chicken &amp; orzo broth</strong> in bowls and drizzle with <strong>olive oil</strong>\u00a0</p> <p>Garnish with the <strong>cheese shavings</strong></p> <p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
